ed of them based on their anticipated roles in society. Referencing school reforms such as No Child Left Behind, Race to the Top, and Common Core, Goyette shows that education is not merely reflective of a society's views, but instrumental in shaping and changing society's structure.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aEducationxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aEducational equalizationzUnited States. 0aEqualityxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520960718423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520960718.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles